1.title: This is the Place
1.plot: On their one-year anniversary of living together, the Bunkheads debate whether or not their situation is sustainable and if it's better to risk their lives topside with the zombies still ravaging the Earth.

2.title: Touch of My Hand
2.plot: A bit fed up with the boys and seeing an opportunity, Dani persuades the guys to leave the bunker so that she can have some "quality" time to herself. Out in the woods, Matt tries to keep the peace.

3.title: Let Me Clear My Throat
3.plot: Kip's never ending "Cold War" with Cash transforms into a full-blown conflict during the first "Bunkheads Presidential Debate." Everything comes to a head when a vote is taken to kick out one of the bunkmates.

4.title: Who's That Girl
4.plot: Out in the real world, Kip discovers an attractive stranger, Blair, and brings her back to the bunker. The group dynamic is thrown out of whack and the Bunkheads have to decide whether to permanently invite Blair into their gang.

5.title: Dreams
5.plot: Riding the coattails of the Sandman, we go inside the Bunkheads' minds for an episode that takes place entirely in sleep. We meet new characters, learn secrets, and experience the majestic and uncontainable glory of Kip's rap performance.

6.title: All My Friends
6.plot: After 2 years of holding everyone together, Matt has a nervous breakdown. The gang tries bring Matt back with the kind of zany skits that he loves. Nothing seems to get through to him until Kip comes up with one last brilliant idea.

imdb.plot outline: With humor and heart, Bunkheads tells the story of the unlikeliest people forging a new family. One year into the zombie apocalypse we jump into an underground bunker where four zany survivors are hiding from the hordes above. This random group includes a floundering actress, a buff computer nerd, a goofball elementary teacher, and an immature wannabe rapper. Stuck in cramped quarters, the Bunkheads are isolated and hangry. As frustrations start to boil over we explore the lives, dreams, and fantasies of these lovable goofballs who aren't sure if they are holding out for a miraculous rescue or just biding time until they become zombie lunchables. As they await their fate, we learn that the hardest part of the zombie apocalypse isn't surviving; it's putting up with each other.
